    "response": "To compute the **sample standard deviation** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{25, 10, 0, 9, -1, -14, -21\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### **Step 1: Find the mean (average) of the data set**\n\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 + (-1) + (-14) + (-21)}{7}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 - 1 - 14 - 21}{7}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{25 + 10 + 9 - 1 - 14 - 21}{7} = \\frac{29}{7}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### **Step 2: Compute the squared differences from the mean**\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(25 - \\frac{29}{7})^2 &= \\left(\\frac{175 - 29}{7}\\right)^2 = \\left(\\frac{146}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{21316}{49} \\\\\n(10 - \\frac{29}{7})^2 &= \\left(\\frac{70 - 29}{7}\\right)^2 = \\left(\\frac{41}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{1681}{49} \\\\\n(0 - \\frac{29}{7})^2 &= \\left(-\\frac{29}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{841}{49} \\\\\n(9 - \\frac{29}{7})^2 &= \\left(\\frac{63 - 29}{7}\\right)^2 = \\left(\\frac{34}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{1156}{49} \\\\\n(-1 - \\frac{29}{7})^2 &= \\left(-\\frac{29 + 7}{7}\\right)^2 = \\left(-\\frac{36}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{1296}{49} \\\\\n(-14 - \\frac{29}{7})^2 &= \\left(-\\frac{98 + 29}{7}\\right)^2"
